annotationA: RNA-binding protein 1; Contributes to the activation of female-specific DSX splicing in vivo by recognizing the RBP1 target sequences within the purine-rich polypyrimidine tract of the female-specific 3' splice site; Belongs to the splicing factor SR family
annotationB: Rbp1-like, isoform B; Nucleotide binding; nucleic acid binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: RNA splicing; mRNA splicing, via spliceosome; mRNA splice site selection
